  "text": "[20] The coagulation scavenging rates were computed for each size bin at each time by using the equation of [CITATION_1] to obtain the second order coagulation rate constants for each pair of particle sizes. Then the pseudo-first order rate constant was obtained by summing the products of the second order rate constant and the measured particle concentration in the appropriate size bin, larger than the one for which k c was being determined. For the relatively modest concentrations of nucleation mode particles observed here, coagulation between the nucleation mode and the accumulation mode is much faster than coagulation within the nucleation mode. Thus, the latter process was neglected in this analysis, which we will later show to be a valid assumption. As a result, the loss of nucleation mode particles can be treated as pseudo-first order.",
