    "96116255": {
      "title": "Brownian coagulation in aerosols-The role of long range forces",
      "abstract": "Abstract A recent solution to Brownian coagulation in a field of force (M.G. Sceats, J. Chem. Phys. 84 , 5206 (1986)) is applied over the entire range of relative particle size for neutral particles interacting through dispersion forces at arbitrary bath gas density. The long range forces manifest themselves through two stability factors W (0) and W (∞), which are readily evaluated for any interaction potential."
